      <h1 class='title'>Family Visitor Appeals</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 11 June 2003 vol 406 c47WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_47ws' title='Col. 47WS &mdash; HC Deb 11 June 2003 vol 406 c47WS' name='column_47ws' href='#column_47ws' rel='bookmark'>47WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0406P0_20030611_CWS_1'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-beverley-hughes' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0406P0_20030611_CWS_1' title='Link to this speech by Ms Beverley Hughes' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-beverley-hughes" title="Ms Beverley Hughes">The Minister for Citizenship and Immigration (Beverley Hughes)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">In January 2001, we announced a review of the family visitor appeal system introduced under the <a href="/acts/immigration-and-asylum-act-1999">Immigration and Asylum Act 1999</a>. The review was undertaken by officials from UK visas, the Lord Chancellor's Department, the Home Office, HM Treasury and the Legal Services Commission. A discussion exercise was held towards the end of 2001 and research was commissioned from the Home Office Research, Development and Statistics Directorate to inform the review.</p><p>I am pleased to announce that the final report of the review team is published today, and has been placed in the Library of the House.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
